01/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase on Saturday (28 February) gave an ultimatum to police who are investigating recent attacks against independent journalists across the country. He demanded that they find the perpetrators by the end of the week or face sanctions, including dismissals of police chiefs. The ultimatum followed criticism from the European Parliament. (BTA - 29/02/04; Rompres - 28/02/04)
